# .agent-frozen — files agents must NOT modify without explicit human approval.
#
# Enforced two ways (E02, decisions §6b):
#   1. CI + local: scripts/check-frozen.mjs fails if any changed file matches an
#      entry below (unless the PR carries the 'frozen-change-approved' label).
#   2. At agent tool-use time: the PreToolUse hook in .claude/settings.json blocks
#      Edit/Write on these paths.
#
# Policy: entries are removed/changed ONLY by an epic explicitly chartered to
# modify that file, in the same PR, ask-first. The 'frozen-change-approved' label
# is the human escape hatch. Lines starting with # are comments; blank lines ignored.
# Globs: * matches within a path segment, ** matches across segments.

# --- Pure, audit-named domain modules (characterization-tested, must stay stable) ---
# json-store.ts UNFROZEN by E05 (P1-E05 plan step 2, the chartered rewrite epic):
# it becomes a thin delegate over src/lib/db/records.ts; the records-parity
# suite carries the old characterization guarantees forward.
src/lib/hours.ts
src/lib/ferry-forecast.ts
src/lib/wsf.ts
src/lib/ferry-reminder.ts
src/lib/ferry-line.ts
src/lib/time.ts

# --- Production data pipelines (NOT CI; scheduled crons) ---
.github/workflows/ferry-observe.yml
.github/workflows/ferry-accuracy.yml

# --- Audit-flagged monoliths (high blast radius; touch only with a chartered epic) ---
# E22 moved the two geoman editors into the (site) route group. Pure `git mv`
# renames — `git diff -M90%` reports R100 for both, i.e. zero content changed —
# so the freeze is intact and only these two lines were repointed. The move
# itself still trips check-frozen (a rename puts BOTH the old and the new path
# in the changed set), which is why the E22 refactor PR carries the
# 'frozen-change-approved' label: the label attests to the rename, not to an edit.
src/components/feature-map.tsx
src/app/(site)/admin/map/editor.tsx
src/app/(site)/admin/maps/editor.tsx
